      "side": 1,
      "message": "You know what?  Let\u0027s double down on this idea and make them functions wherever you use them instead of putting them in SkVx.h.  I still feel uneasy about providing methods like this that strongly favor one architecture over others.  If we promote load2/load4, people will think they\u0027re a good idea to use in general, where they\u0027re really a last resort for when you can\u0027t rearrange your data, or if you want to favor ARM and don\u0027t mind handicapping all other architectures.",
      "parentUuid": "19ccf66a_65380067",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 90,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 99,
        "endChar": 5
      },
